This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a metric learning technique for classification. The use of kernel functions also suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of feature vectors and concatenation of features suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the mention of hierarchical learning structures suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
